President Biden delivered a speech at the Martin Luther King, Jr. Memorial in Washington, D.C., highlighting the ongoing struggle for equality and justice in America. He emphasized the need to live up to the ideals of the Declaration of Independence and called for progress in areas such as economic justice, healthcare, education, and voting rights. The President also addressed the issues of hate crimes and domestic terrorism, particularly white supremacy, and pledged to take comprehensive action to combat these threats. He concluded by urging Americans to continue fighting for equality and to honor the legacy of Dr. King.